 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=naladini>naladini</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://img.ranchoweb.com/images/naladini/pills.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 863<br> <font color=#333333>(2/23/03 5:40:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm28.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1271.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: charms</span><hr size=1> They never really release info like that ahead of time. Odds are, most will be NO Drop. As always, there's really no reason to have a no drop flag from a roleplay perspective, and one of these days, they should consider getting rid of it. Maybe they'll finally do so when they stop selling expansions/extensions.<br>
<br>
I'm kind of curious as to how much current gear might get flagged as charm enabled (eg. some neck slot items).<br>
<br>
Since it is a new inventory slot, I'd imagine they'll be adding charms to several areas of the game, including VT and Elemental Planes.<br>
<br>
 <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=381929"> Naladini </a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
Conjurer of the 58th Season-Stormhammer<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://img.ranchoweb.com/images/naladini/pills.gif" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=krilenspiritlink>Krilen Spiritlink</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 714<br> <font color=#333333>(2/23/03 6:38:10 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm28.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1271.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: charms</span><hr size=1> I'm guessing charms will be mostly or fully tradeskill or quest items. <p>Happy trails.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=thedwellerindarkness@themagicianstower>thedwellerindarkness</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 477<br> <font color=#333333>(2/23/03 8:45:58 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm28.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1271.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: charms</span><hr size=1> Well charms were sold as being a LoK feature. Since eveyone already has the charm inventory slot, the only way they can make them a LoK feature is if they only drop (or the tradeskill parts drop) in LoK. Otherwise it's a feature for everyone that just happens to go live at the release of LoK.<br>
<br>
I doubt any old items will be changed to be charms. The focus items updated old equipment so that class balance could be implemented without forcing EVERY caster into the same zones fighting for drops. Charms don't look to be a balance shifting piece of equipment, so I expect it's just easier to make new items than to flag old items and give everyone charms for free.<br>
<br>
I'm not going to compete with people on getting charms in LoK. I'm going to start a froggy cleric to pal with my mage, and worry about charms later. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=izudin@themagicianstower>Izudin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 301<br> <font color=#333333>(2/23/03 9:22:58 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm28.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1271.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Hmm</span><hr size=1> Take a look at the examples here:<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://everquest.station.sony.com/legacy/f_charms.jsp">everquest.station.sony.co...charms.jsp</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
These are not no drop. From what I understand charms will be craftable, so they will most likely not be no drop.<br>
<br>
Izudin<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=casmx>CasmX</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.rpgrevelation.com/board/levels/12.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 110<br> <font color=#333333>(2/23/03 11:03:39 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm28.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1271.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Hmm</span><hr size=1> honestly I think charms is the best thing about this expansion. Imagine the coldain prayer shawl as a charm with say...faction. Your faction with Coldain is scowling, you get shawl 1. Threatening, shawl 2. Dubious, 3. amiably, 4. Indiff, 5. kindly, 6. warmly, 7. ally, 8th. (not sure if i went in the right order, but u get the idea) This may be a drastic example, but from what I understand, charms would work similar to that. A charm is more like a 'living' item (for lack of a better term) always changing depending on a certain aspect of your character. I look forward to it. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=573070" target="top">Casm</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tenner>tenner</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 69<br> <font color=#333333>(2/23/03 12:27:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm28.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1271.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Hmm</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><